  "body": "#### Context\r\n\r\nLocation: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/1fa91729f2a591df2baf2dc77e81711a6e61c028/accounts/abi/argument.go#L118\r\ngo-ethereum version: v1.10.12 (using go-ethereum as a go module)\r\n\r\n#### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen calling [`args.Copy(v, values)`](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/1fa91729f2a591df2baf2dc77e81711a6e61c028/accounts/abi/argument.go#L118) with `len(values) == 1`, this function calls `args.copyAtomic(v, values[0])`.\r\n\r\nIf `v` is a struct, `args.copyAtomic` then calls `set(dst.Field(0), src)`, attempting to assign the value to the first field of the struct, whereas it should instead assign the value to the struct itself.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n```go\r\npackage test\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n\t\"testing\"\r\n\r\n\t\"github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/accounts/abi\"\r\n)\r\n\r\ntype Frame struct {\r\n\tA, B uint64\r\n}\r\n\r\nvar FrameType = func() abi.Type {\r\n\tt, err := abi.NewType(\r\n\t\t\"tuple\",\r\n\t\t\"Frame\",\r\n\t\t[]abi.ArgumentMarshaling{\r\n\t\t\t{Type: \"uint64\", Name: \"A\"},\r\n\t\t\t{Type: \"uint64\", Name: \"B\"},\r\n\t\t},\r\n\t)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tpanic(err)\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn t\r\n}()\r\n\r\nfunc TestPackUnpack(t *testing.T) {\r\n\tframeArgs := abi.Arguments{\r\n\t\t{Name: \"Frame\", Type: FrameType},\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tsrc := Frame{A: 0, B: 1}\r\n\tb, err := frameArgs.Pack(src)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"Packing: %v\", err)\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tvalues, err := frameArgs.Unpack(b)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"unpacking: %v\", err)\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tvar dst Frame\r\n\terr = frameArgs.Copy(&dst, values)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"copying: %v\", err)\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```",
