    "body": "The copy function will move the decoded value into the content receiver. The receiver is expected to be a wrapper(e.g. a struct) and the fields in the receiver correspond to the decoded value one-to-one. \r\n\r\nIf there is only a single struct value, so the receiver is expected to be something like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntype struct ResultWrapper {\r\n    F Frame\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe single decoded value will be set to the `F` field.",
